Quote:   In view of the present uncertainty [of descent] it seems undesirable to use either the names ferret or polecat as these refer to specific overseas forms. It is proposed to adopt provisionally the vernacular name of `fitch'. <i>Ibid.</i> 74 Ferret skins are known to the manufacturer as the New Zealand Fitch.
